Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content:
Not sure how it is put across in the curriculum, but here’s my opinion.

Yes, risk free rate is considered as the starting point to determine potential returns from different investments. Assess the risk of those potential investments, add a risk premium to the risk free rate to derive a broad understanding of what the returns of alternate investment could look like. In no way it can be used for comparing returns of investments cause risk free rates have negligible amount of risk, whereas other investments holds risks.

Secondly, benchmark rates are commonly referred to as inter bank lending rates or rates set by Central Banks (Fed / RBI etc). We see repo rates here, there are LIBOR/ MIBOR rates and so on. These are called benchmark rates.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of chapter 4
Interest rate
Treasury rate :- 
Rate that are on government issued security.risk free rate are reference rate.
Corporate bonds = treasury + spread 
Spread is for the risk of the bond over the government rate
Libor :- 
Under U.K. regulatory oversight since 2012
* Reflects the rate at which unsecured loans can be obtained between banks in the interbank money market.
Interbank money market :- market for loan and deposit between banks for maturities upto 1 year.
Process :- 8-16 banks submit daily rates they believe they could borrow at for 5 currencies and 7 times periods.
Libor :- is not a single rate it is a family of rates.
Highest/lowest 25% of bid dicarded
Libor = mean of mid 50 % of bids
Fed funds rate :- 
Banks lending (surplus) to banks (shortage) overnight rate called federal fund rate.
Weighted average of all the sum of all the loans the rate on all the loans is called effective federal funds rate.
Repo rate :- 
Libor and fed rate are unsecure but repo rate is secured loan.
Repurchase agreement :- 
A will sell a security to B and B will give funds to A and when it repurchase it will give amount with interest on it. If security provide any interest it will belong to A 
B is having reverse repurchase agreement. There will be credit risk associated so fund lent is less than the value of security and this difference is called repo margin.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's learning
Chapter 5 
Forward/future price :-
Investment :- 
* Stocks, bonds, precious metals
* It is something you own for it's sake. You hold it for its value for its stream of income.
Consumption asset :- 
* Buy for use , you don't hold it for income or future value
* Example copper, wheat, oil and corn
We differentiated them because they require different pricing argument
Short selling :- 
Requires a margin account 
Assumptions for pricing models 
* No transaction cost
* Same tax rate on all the trading profits
* Borrow and lend at the same risk free rate
* Arbitrage opportunity are taken :- it implies ability and willingness to pick it up.
Forward price : Investment asset 
Case 1 :- No income
Let current price be 40 
Time to expiration = 3 months
Risk free interest rate= 5% 
Borrow 40 at r for 0.25 years
Owe 40*e^0.25*0.05 = 40.5 in 3 months
If future price  is greater than 40.5 
Buy So and sell future contract.
Or if So for 40 invest for r for 0.25 years have 40.5 in 3 months 
If Fo is less than 40.5 then sell So and buy Fo
If F = S*e^rt means no arbitrage
Always remember buy less sell high

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's learning
Case 2 
Known income:- 
Let So be 900 
 it pays income of 40 in 4 months.
Time 9 months.
Let's borrow 900 
Calculating the present value of 40 which is continuously compounded comes to be 39.6
Now seeing this we are borrowing (900-39.6)= 860.40 which becomes after 9 months = 886.40
If Fo is greater than 886.40  
buy So 
sell Fo
Profit = Fo - (So - I)e^rt
I = net present value of income

If Fo is less than 886.40
Sell at So
Buy Fo
Profit = (So - I )e^rt - Fo

Content:
Case 3 
Known yield 
Let q be the average yield during Life of contract
6 months forward contract
Rate of interest = 10 %
q = 2% per 6 month period i.e, 4% per annum
For future price calculation we need Rc.
Rc = mln(1+ Rm/m)
Let So = 25
T = 0.5 yr
Rc= 3.96%
Fo = So * e^{r-q}*t
Fo = 25.77
Will require buy low and sell high approach to get our position

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
•  future are simply zero sum game
•  payoff of forward is linear and mirror image for buyer and seller
•  once we enter forward agreement there is no obligation to stick to the contact until the expiry
•  it is daily settled
•  open interest is a number that tells you how many contract are currently standing
•  volume is the total number of contract formed
•  OI can increase or decrease but volume always increases.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Revised previous goal today :- 
• Forward contract lays down the basic foundation for future contract
•  Forward is OTC derivative , not traded in exchange
•  forward are private agreement whose terms vary from one contract to other
•  settlement takes place in two ways :- cash settlement and physical settlement
•  futures reduce risk of forward namely counterparty risk and liquity risk
•  the core of forward and future are same
•  forward or future gives you financial benefits if you have accurate directional view of an asset price
•  future price generally mimic the underlying price of spot matket
•  unlike Forward future are tradable
•  future contract is standardized wherein all variable of the agreement are predetermined
•  most future contract are cash settled
•  SEBI in india regulates forward market
•  lot size is minimum quantity specified in future contract
•  to enter a forward contract both buyer and seller should maintain a margin in their account
•  margin has two components span and exposure. 
•  exposure compenent of margin changes as the volatility increase
•  NSE has 3 different contract of same underlying which expires in 3 consecutive months
•  calendar spread is a technique which involves buying a certain month contract and selling another month contract simultaneously for same underlying
•  when calendar spread is initiated margins required are lower since the risk is drastically reduced
•  Margin allow us to deposit a small amount and Take exposure to a large value transaction
•  spot market transactions are not leverage we can transact to the extent of our capital
•  higher the leverage hingher risk and higher the chance of making money

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Options
• Option is a tool for protecting your position and risk
• at agreement time buyer pays a certain amount to seller called margin
• agreement happen at a pre specified price called strike price
• option buyer will benefits only if the price of the asset increase than the strike price
• statistically option seller has higher odds of winning in an typical option contract
• exercising of an option contract is the act of claiming your right to buy option contract at the end of expiry
• similar to future, option contract expires on last Thursday of every month
• premium are not fixed they vary based on several factors
• option are cash settled in india
• maximum loss of call buyer is the premium paid
• maximum profit is unlimited for option buyer

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Revision 
* Delta is rate of change in price of an option for every 1 point move in price of underlying.
* Delta of call option is (0-1).
* Delta of put option is (-1,0).
* New option price = Old option price + Delta*(new underlying price - old underlying price).
* Delta represent the probability of option expiring ITM.
* ITM call delta ranges from 0.5 to 1 .
* ATM call delta is 0.5 .
* OTM call delta ranges from 0 to 0.5 .
* ITM put delta ranges from -0.5 to -1 .
* ATM put delta is -0.5  .
* OTM put delta ranges from -1 to -0.5 .
* Delta of underlying is 1.
* Option having higher delta are more responsive to change in price of underlying.
* For ITM ,delta of an option closer to expiry is higher and vice-versa.
* For OTM ,delta of an option closer to expiry is lower and vice-versa.
* For ATM ,delta of an option closer to expiry is lower and vice-versa.
* For ITM ,delta of an option higher if low volatility and vice-versa.
* For OTM ,delta of an option higher means high volatility.
* Value of delta keeps changing as other variables do 
* Important : call delta + put delta = 1.

Author: anuraj#0290
Content:
Hello I am Anuraj, from NIT Bhopal.
Here is my opinion about rat racing, in colleges most of the students are confused and don't know what they should do for their interest. So, generally whenever we are confused and don't know where to go, we just follow what our fellows are doing. Same, happens in this case. And, in my opinion the best way to cope up with the rat racing is to don't rush in the starting of your college life for placements or internships. Take your time and explore different fields patiently. Then, you will come to know which field interests you the most.
My biggest problem in college -
1. Lack of students having the same mindset as mine.
2. No proper guidance, if I want to choose a field other than engineering.
3. No free time to explore different fields.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's learning
• Buy a put option when you are bearish about underlying
• intrinsic value = strike price- spot price
• P and L of a put option buyer can be calculated as max(0, strike price- spot price)- premium paid
• breakeven point for put option buyer is strike - premium paid
• buy a call option or sell a put option when you expect market to go up
• buy a put option or sell a call option when you expect market to go down
• buyer of an option has unlimited profit and limited loss
• seller of an option has unlimited risk and limited profit
• premium is a function of option greek
• market control the option greek and the Greeks variation itself
• any option having an intrinsic value is classified as in the money
• any option does not having intrinsic value is classified as on the money
• if strike price is almost equal to spot price is called at the money
• when the intrinsic value is very high, it is called deep itm
• when the intrinsic value is least, it is called deep otm
• premium for itm option are always higher than premium for otm option

Author: infinity ♾#0542
Content:
Time flies. And it literally does when you are in college. That is the biggest problem I have faced in my college life.  When you have personality of an explorer, a dreamer, you have to manage your time very precisely or else your exploration will never reach any milestones. I know that many of you might be facing this problem of time management. I will recommend a wonderful trick that can change your life and believe me when I say this because I have tried tens of things in past 2.5 years and only this worked. buy a simple smartwatch, which will cost around 1500, don't worry it's investment on yourself. Now download and application like Google tasks where you can schedule your targets and get notified on your watch with a little vibration throughout the day. This way even if you are not able to complete your tasks with an efficiency of 100% your subconscious mind will at least get to know that these things are to be done.

 If not today, you will do it tomorrow but you will definitely do that task and the task will not get disappeared in that flying time.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's revision
Theta
* Theta measure impact of time on price of option.
* Theta is defined as change in option price for a one unit change in time left to expiration.
* Theta is defined as lost of option value as a result of time decay.
* Time decay is the rate at which the value of an option erodes with each passing day.
* Theta works in favour of option writer and against option buyer
* Theta is negative for long position and positive for short position.
* Price of an option reduces each day by theta.
* Call value erode slightly Higher than put.
* ATM 
* has highest theta
* Theta increase in absolute value with passing days , before starting to rise exponentially as expiration gets closer.
* ATM is risky because of rapid declining theta will rapidly erode time value of option.
* ITM
* Intrinsic value form larger component
* Have low theta , deep ITM have low loss in terms of time value.
* Theta tends to increase at slower rate, before starting to fall sharply as expiry gets closer 
* OTM 
* Have only time value no intrinsic value
* Deep OTM , lower time value lower theta
* Theta increase at slower rate before exponential decrease
* Higher volatility, higher time value of an option , higher option value.
* Fall in time value of option with high volatility tends to be greater than fall in time value option with low volatility.
* Low volatility, fall in time value is steadier.

Author: mewtwo#5793
Content:
Hello everyone,

I have completed my Goal 5 in Data Science. It was fun to complete this goal.

Here is my learning for this topic.

- After completing supervised learning in previous goals, This goal was a bit new for me as it was based on unsupervised learning.
- In this goal, I learned about Clustering algorithms in detail to identify clusters among data and thus predict the nature of new data.
- I also learned about PCA in detail and the maths behind it was fascinating as it was based on the significance of eigenvectors.
- Then I learned about the two most famous jargon in machine learning field which are SVM (support vector machines) and SVD( singular Vector Decomposition )
- SVMs are used basically for classification problems and the maths behind this uses higher dimensions and hyperplanes.. (which was very fascinating on one side... but it made me revise the linear algebra terms again 😉 )

I can't say I have a tight grip on these two, but the earlier ones are on the comfortable side for me. Also, the project given this time was too helpful in providing confidence in the implementation of clustering...

All in all, this project was full of small implementations which boost my inner self as I proceed.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's revision
* Volatility is rate at which price of an asset fluctuate over time.
* Historical volatility measures the dispersion around mean for daily returns on an Annualised basis.
* Implied volatility is measure of future volatility.
* Vega is defined as change in option price for every 1% change in implied volatility.
* Higher the IV higher would be change in option price.
* Buyer of a call or put benefit when IV go up.
* Seller of a call or put benefit when IV go down.
* Vega is positive for long position and negative for short position.
* Long means you have long vega exposure and short means you have short vega exposure.
* Rising volatility works against option seller.
* Vega is identical for all call and put.
* Vega impacts only time value component of option price that is extrinsic value not the Intrinsic value.
* Higher time to expiration, higher would be vega
* Vega is highest for ATM.
* As moving either ITM or OTM vega starts declining
* Vega is too low for deep ITM and OTM.
* Maximum impact of change in IV tends to occur for options that are ATM because they tend to have highest vega.
* Closer the probability of option expiring ITM moves towards extreme lower will be vega

Content:
🌟 Streak Day #3
So since a couple of hours, I'm not feeling like doing anything. I am feeling the restlessness and the urge to do something, but don't have the urge to think of what to do.
And even if I start thinking of something, no task comes to my mind , not even those in my day plan

I feel like these are the mystery moments through which I can discover something. But then again, I am clueless

Have any of you been in this state?

Author: Ginie#9606
Content:
Truly speaking I have been in this state for maximum time since lockdown. 
Making list of the things beforehand of all that one loves to do can be of great help... It can be as simple as cooking something for ourselves ( which gives great joy) or stuff like that. 
Because in these times of restlessness, no meditation or focus techniques are of help.
So reaching out to that list and picking up any task that u feel is the best for that time can help u get out of the situation.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Volatility :- swings
* Frequency and severity with which the market price of an investment fluctuate. More market swing means more volatility.
Implied volatility
* Represent how volatile the stock will be in near future. IV increase so making big move of underlying
Put IV is greater than call IV
On the money (faraway) : IV increase a lot
IV rank :( Today iv -low)/(high-low)*100
IV percentile : what% of days the IV was low in last 1 year.
Historical volatility: 
Looks at past events
Implied volatility:
Predict future volatility
IV tends to overstate the actual expected move nearly every stock in long term.
Options are overpriced because of volatility and if market do not fluctuate that much sellers make a lot of money.
HV : 
HV is a measure of how volatile the price movement of a security has been
during a certain period of time.
Expressed in terms of standard deviations.
IV : 
IV is a measure of how volatile the stock will be in future.
IV depends on supply and demand in market.
HV-IV Divergence
An HV-IV divergence occurs when HV declines and IV rises or vice versa.
Expected stock volatility:
Yearly standard deviations can be related to that of one day or one week by dividing the standard deviations for 1 year by sqrt of number of trading days that year to calculate for one day
 and multiply number of trading days sqrt to calculate for 1 month.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Revision notes
Financial markets
1- Exchange traded : individual trade standardized. Contracts that have been defined on the exchange. Traders are physically present, retail investors.
Over the counter : Trading is done over phone or computer system. Trading between two large financial institutions or between financial institution and client.

Securities and contract 
1- Basic securities
a - Fixed income (bonds)
b - Equities (Stocks)
2- Derivatives and contract
a - Forward/Futures
b - Swaps
c - Options

Bonds - fixed income securities, gives owner the right to a fixed, pre-determined payment,at a future pre-determined date.

Types of bonds:- 
Depending on maturity
1- Short term bonds (less than 1 year)
2- Long term bonds (more than 1 year)
Depending on payment
1- Pure discount bonds : involves only initial payment
2 - Coupon bonds : Periodic payment
Pure discount bonds are below par ( price at which bond is sold is lower than nominal value)

Risks associated with bonds: 
1- Credit risk
2- Inflation risk
3- liquidity risk
Stocks :
Security that gives it's owner right to proportion of any profit that might be distributed by the firm that issue the stock.

Dividend 
1- Random
2- depending on firm's profit
Two sources of return: 
1- Dividend until ownership (dividend gain)
2- difference between price at which stock was sold and was purchased(Capital gain)

Short selling: borrowing stock then selling it and hope that price will fall in future, in future buy it for low price and return.

Future and forwards:
Contracts where one party agrees to buy underlying asset at a future pre-determined date at a predetermined price

2- Swaps : Contract by which two parties exchange cash flows

3- Options : It gives owner the right to buy or sell another security on or before a predetermined future date for a predetermined price

Call : owner has right to buy underlying
Put : owner has right to sell underlying
European : owner of option can buy/ sell assets at fixed price

word: **distinction**

**meaning and usage:**
__well known usage:__ something different from the rest

- You can clearly see the distinction among the art forms around Europe.

__academic/formal usage:__ excelling in something, again means that it stands out from the rest

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
🌟 Streak Day #5:
Found one good way to tame distractions today. So I have been at my friend's work city since the last 2 days. 
New city presents new environment, new questions, new things to be curious about, new people and their new perspectives. 

So, this amount of newness often can lead to you questioning yourself and your decisions. You might begin to doubt yourself. 
The secret I found to tackle these muddling distractions is 
1. to question the thought the moment it comes in your head instead of accepting it as truth.
2. Then give yourself some time without reaching any conclusion.

I applied these two techniques and now after 2 days, I'm unaffected by these distractions
😬 😇

Content:
@everyone for those having exams these days, I would strongly suggest you to consciously decide what you want to do just after giving the exam.

Looking forward to hear about this from you all

Author: Rishabh Jain#5994
Content:
Hello everyone, I am Rishabh. This is the first time I am conversing in meditation channel. Back in COVID times, I was intrigued with inner sciences, I would watch up spiritual gurus on YouTube most of the time. One of them, Sadhguru really appealed to me. And I decided to take up the inner engineering program offered by the Isha Foundation. They thaught numerous practices in the program, the best of them being Shambhavi Mahamudra Kriya. I got initiated into the same by Sadhguru on 13th of February,2022. I have kept up my practice since the day. Today is 133rd day and I have missed the practice only twice. 
On the day of the initiation, I did experienced things which would have normally be seen absurd. But it is something which is true to my experience. My experience of the practice is mixed. Sometimes it's really great, I wouldn't wish to stop it. Sometimes I wanted to complete it as fast as possible. But one thing is for sure, I have seen myself growing out of my fears and compulsions, just by practicing the kriya correctly. The program costs around 5K rupees, and if any of you is willing to take up the program and have any doubts regarding it or are uncertain, I would say it is one of investment you should make upon yourself and give it a shot, without any expectations as such. Simply make the investment and attend the program whole heartedly. I am sure you will make something wonderful out of the program. 🙏

Author: kb0304#9864
Content:
I'm Karan, IITR 2019 passout.
The Rat race is getting very real, not just in college but even after college in the world around us. In college people pursue placements, and with the same rat-race mindset they continue pursuing "promotions", "salary hikes", etc. in the future.. by mindlessly switching companies or by just working on things that they are not happy or passionate about. In college students, the rat race has increased so much because of the gap between mentors and mentees, especially due to the virtualization of college in the past year, students getting mentorship from mentors who themselves are driven by fear. We all need to learn to listen to our heart and follow it in different aspects of life, as always it will guide us in the right direction. 

Top problems, currently in life. (or goals)
1. Physical Health
2. Emotional Strength
3. Independence

Author: kb0304#9864

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's revision
Bull call spread :- 
* Spread are multi leg strategies involving 2 or more options.
* Bull call is best when outlook for stock is moderate, could be moderately bullish or bearish
* Spread strategies
 1- protects from downside cases
2 - amount of profit that we will make is also predictable
 3- As a trade off, get to participate in market for lesser cost.
* Comes in hand when we have moderately bullish view on stock.
* To implement bull call spread  
 1- buy one ATM call option
 2- Sell one OTM call option
* What to ensure
 1- Stocks belong to same underlying
 2- Belong to same expiry series
 3- each leg involve same number of options
* When spot price is less than both options strike price and when spot price is less than OTM strike but equal to ATM strike price then loss happens but is limited to a certain value
*  When spot price is greater than both options strike price and when spot price is greater than ATM strike but equal to OTM strike price then profit happens but is limited to a certain value.
* Spread = difference of higher and lower strike price.
* Bull call max spread loss = net debit of strategy
* Bull call maximum profit = spread - net debit.
* Breakeven point = lower strike + net debit
* Theta plays important role in strike selection
* Risk reward gets skewed based on strike you choose.
Bull put spread :- 
* Difference in Bull Call spread in terms of strategy execution and strike selection.
* Bull put spread involved creating spread by ' Put option' rather than call option.
* Bull call spread is executed for debit, bull put spread executed for a credit.
* When to go with Bull Put spread
 1 - Markets have declined considerably
 2 - Volatility is on the higher side
 3 - Plenty of time to expiry 
* To implement
* Buy 1 OTM Put option
* Sell 1 OTM Put option
* What to ensure
 1- All strike belong to same underlying
 2- Belong to same expiry series
 3- each leg involve same number of options.

Author: utkarsh#1616
Content:
Read about **The Five Whys**

The 5 Whys technique is an effective tool for root-cause analysis in the Lean philosophy. It is utilized by individuals and teams to protect their processes from recurring mistakes.  

The methodology, developed by Sakichi Toyoda in 1930, was originally used in the Toyota Production System. Asking why five times helped the team at Toyota to identify the nature of the problem and find a clear solution. 

When feel stuck in problem ask 5 why sequentially 💡

Author: satyam_dubey#3256
Content:
That is definitely the biggest obstacle people face in their journey of following Passion... 
People have this feeling in mind that they won't be able achieve financial freedom following their passion!

This used to be my problem too for a long time..

But I realised it over time that it's mostly a midnset belief problem.

If you see how money works..
Money = value creation.

If you create value for people/company through your skills.
People give you money in exchange.

So, if you are confident enough that you can create value in people's/company's life through what you love...

Money is just the by product.

The focus of needs to shift from Money to Value.
That's it. That's the magical key 🌟

Lastly... Faith is the most expensive thing! 
Pays you the most. The more absolute your faith is the higher is the return ❤️

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's revision
Black scholes model
* It is differential equation widely used to price option contract.
* It requires 5 input variables, strike price of an option, current stock price, Time to expiration, risk free rate and volatility.
* Due to certain assumptions price deviate from real world results.
* Only used in European option as it doesn't take into account that American option can be exercised before time to expiration.
* BSM posits that instrument, such as stock shares or future contact, will have lognormal distribution of prices following a random walk with constant drift and Volatility.
* It is theoretically possible for option seller to set rational prices for the option that they are selling.
* Model predicts that the price of heavily traded asset follow a geometric browninan motion with constant Volatility and drift.
Assumptions :- 
* No dividend are paid out during the life of an option.
* Markets are random
* There are no transactions costs in buying an option.
* Risk free rate and volatility of the underlying asset are known and constant
* Returns on the underlying asset are log- normally distributed
* Option is European and can be only exercise at expiration.
Volatility skew :- 
* BSM assume stock price follow lognormal distribution because asset prices cannot be negative.
* Asset prices are observed to have significant right skewness and some degree of kutosis. This means high risk Downward moves often happens in market than normal distribution.
Drawback :-
* Used for only European call and do not consider American option can be exercised before expiration.
* Assume dividend and risk free rate are constant, but this may not be true in reality.
* Model also assume volatility remain constant over option life.

Author: vedant11#6910
Content:
this is an interesting word since I have seen it getting used in many sentences

**word**: culminate

**meaning and usage:**

- reach the conclusion or climax
---> The Marias band tour will __culminate__ in Miami.

- reach the highest, the peak or the most decisive point
---> DiCaprio's fan-following __culminated__ when he won the Oscar's award.

- to involve the highest amount of something
---> Continued miscommunication __culminated__ frustration among them.

- to rise
---> Tsunami waves __culminated__ and fell at an astonishing rate.

Author: Priyanshu Solanki#0864
Content:
Actually in the first version i have made a invisible boundary so that the ball cannot move to the right of the screen as well as i have made separate scripts for camera and the borders. And the ground tile was getting destroyed after a few seconds when the ball touch it

In version 2 i have attached a script to the camera that will follow the player and i had removed the invisible boundary. And now the ground tile will get destroyed after the ball moves certain distance from it. Same fir the background. Also i have added the coins for pickup.

Author: vedant11#6910
Content:
#journaling @Keshav Bidawatka 

Why I like twitter

it's like conversing to people irl
- people understand a single thing in multiple ways
- people try to comment things that add no apparent value to the conversation (humour or insights) but just to show what they know (facts or vocabulary)
- shows how you need to talk appropriately  and differently according to the context, situation
- you learn to give validation to people and it is not a bad thing to do, to let go of correcting them
- empathy
- the way everyone sees the thread in a different tone: depressing, funny, serious, etc.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Bull put spread :- 
* Difference in Bull Call spread in terms of strategy execution and strike selection.
* Bull put spread involved creating spread by ' Put option' rather than call option.
* Bull call spread is executed for debit, bull put spread executed for a credit.
* When to go with Bull Put spread
 1 - Markets have declined considerably
 2 - Volatility is on the higher side
 3 - Plenty of time to expiry 
* To implement
* Buy 1 OTM Put option
* Sell 1 OTM Put option
* What to ensure
 1- All strike belong to same underlying
 2- Belong to same expiry series
 3- each leg involve same number of options.
* Spread = Difference between higher and lower strike price
* Bull put spread max loss = spread - net credit
* Net credit = premium recieved for higher strike - paid for lower strike
* Bull put spread max profit = net credit
* Breakeven point = higher strike- net credit
* Higher the spread, higher the profit potential , higher the breakeven.

.skip -- skips current song
.remove [song index] -- remove the song having the index as in the queue
.voteskip -- to do the voting in order to skip a song
.loop -- to play the songs in the queue on loop

Author: Divyansh#4279
Content:
Confused? How to go about exploration?
We've got you covered... Just follow the steps below 😁
1. Register yourself in passion hunt @ register.explorin.io 
2. Introduce yourself in intros and get a heartwarming welcome from the dreamer's community. 
3. Complete the Mission 1 of "Get the Dreamer Mindset"
- Goal-1 in college-life-problems 
- Goal-2 in core-triggers 
- Goal-3 in passion-vs-ratrace 
4. Complete the Mission 2 of "Get the Dreamer Mindset"
- All goals on exploration-without-explorin.
5. Welcome onboard for Career Exploration as an Ideal Dreamer. (Get access to text in all channels)
6. Experience project-based & discussion-based learnings with a caring community.
7. Clear level-1 & level-2 to get industry ready and get connected with industry opportunities to attain financial security.

If you face any problems in your journey, feel free to drop it in ask-anything.

@Potential Dreamers

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Bear put spread
* Spreads tend to shrink profitability but gives greater visibility on risk.
* It is equivalent to bull call spread.
* Would implement a bear put spread when market outlook is moderately bearish.
* Implementing bear put spread
1- Buy ITM put option
2- Buy OTM put option
* No compulsion that bear put spread has to be created with ITM and OTM option, can be created with any two put option.
* Both Options should belong to same expiry and same underlying.
* Strategy makes loss if spot moves above breakeven point and profit Below the breakeven point.
* Both profits and loss are capped.
* Spread is the difference between two strikes price
* Net debit = Premium paid- premium recieved
* Breakeven = higher strike- lower strike
* Max profit = spread - net debit
* Max loss = net debit
* Positive delta represent strategy is bullish.
* Delta neutral strategy are immune to market directional move, they react to changes in volatility and time, hence these are called " Volatility based strategies" .
* Effects of volatility
1- strategy doesn't vary much with increase in volatility when there is ample time to expiry.
2- cost to strategy varies moderately with increase of volatility when there is 15 days to expiry.
3- cost of strategy varies significantly with increase in volatility when there is about 5 days to expiry

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
I can clearly see incremental improvements from your previous deck Mohit🌟 
Again a very interesting problem statement! And you came up with interesting solutions too.

Improvements on which you can work on:
1. Firstly, you can actually talk to the users and check reviews of the product, so as to show on the deck that you have come up with personas based on real user input.
2. The theme on which you have bucketed the user personas can be shown clearer by showing all the 3 personas together.
3. You can compare the solutions by creating a table showing the pain points solved by each solution. Also, you can try mentioning the reasons behind your RICE scores
4. Success metrics can be explained instead of just mentioning them. For example, the first metric you have shown is "the number of first transactions'. But how would we know that the change in the number of first transactions is actually due to the improvement made?

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Bull put spread :- 
* Difference in Bull Call spread in terms of strategy execution and strike selection.
* Bull put spread involved creating spread by ' Put option' rather than call option.
* Bull call spread is executed for debit, bull put spread executed for a credit.
* When to go with Bull Put spread
 1 - Markets have declined considerably
 2 - Volatility is on the higher side
 3 - Plenty of time to expiry 
* To implement
* Buy 1 OTM Put option
* Sell 1 OTM Put option
* What to ensure
 1- All strike belong to same underlying
 2- Belong to same expiry series
 3- each leg involve same number of options.
* Spread = Difference between higher and lower strike price
* Bull put spread max loss = spread - net credit
* Net credit = premium recieved for higher strike - paid for lower strike
* Bull put spread max profit = net credit
* Breakeven point = higher strike- net credit
* Higher the spread, higher the profit potential , higher the breakeven.

Author: Tarun_17#4341
Content:
Hola *Fam 💙*

Hope everyone is doing best 🔥

Today is my Last day as Intern, I'm elated to announce that I received **PPO as Quant Trader 👨‍💻**
without Explorin I wouldn't have climbed these heights, this is the place where I had been empowered to live my Dream Life❤️‍🔥
Today, I was emotional leaving the company can't even express my feeling how sad I felt leaving
As a Quant, I had helped top traders with their strategy analysis and data-backed hypothesis proving, I had made great bonding with them ❤
Going to miss 
- 9:13 AM IST Prayer 🙏
- 9:15 AM IST opening bell scenes 💱
- 11:30 AM IST lunch with Team 💛
- 12:30 PM IST round table meeting 🤞
- 3:15-3:30 PM IST volatile scenes 🔥
- 4:00 PM IST Post market analysis 🕞
- 5:30 PM IST TT 🏓
- 9:00 PM call with Manager ✨

Literally, tears dropped out of my eyes while penning this 😢 such a lovely experience had
So, called Dream Internship 💕

Thank You, Fam 💙 for being with me in every situation
It's Time, I wish to see you living Dream Life
We would be there with you all Forever 💖

Me being from B.Plan Branch from NIT Bhopal, I Hope you People even don't know that branch exists, I proved that we could Live Life whatever we deserve provided we would give our best with laser focus 🔥 in every situation
"Faith breeds courage"
Mark my words you are going to achieve all of your dreams one day. This is what @Explorin  (My Krishna) Sir said
We Proved ❤
Thank you @Prashant Jindal  💙 for your constant support, even though we had lows in between, I still remember the days when you interviewed by creating a real Interview experience which made me Gain Confidence and a Fearless attitude
Let's this fuckin world know the power of explorin community 🔥

On top of all, I'm gonna miss this Sexiest Desk 🔥 👇

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Short straddle :- 
* Losses are uncapped.
* Just have to sell ATM call and put option.
* Options should belong to same underlying, same expiry and of same strike.
* Maximum profit occurs at ATM strike.
* Strategy remain profitable only between lower and higher breakdown.
* The losses are unlimited in either direction of market movement.
* Upper breakdown = ATM+ net premium
* Lower breakdown = ATM - net premium
* Short straddle works best when market are expected to be in a range and not really Expected to make large moves.
* This strategy is delta neutral
* Volatility should be high at time of strategy execution.
* Volatility should decrease during the holding period of strategy.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
The long and short strangle
* Strangle is an improvisation over straddle, mainly to reduce cost implementation.
* Buy 1 OTM call and put option.
* Strangle is market neutral
* Both Options should belong to same underlying, same expiry.
* Execution should happen in same ratio.
* Few things to generalise
1- max loss is restricted to the net premium paid
2- loss would be maximum between the two strike.
3- upper breakeven point= CE strike+ net premium paid
4- lower breakeven point = PE strike - net premium paid
5- profit potential is unlimited
* Effects of Greek
* Volatility should be low at time of strategy execution
* Volatility should increase during holding period of strategy.
* Market should make large moves direction doesn't matter
* Expected move in time bound
* Short strangle
* Sell OTM call and put option
* Strategy results in loss when the market move in any direction.
* Strategy remain profitable, between lower and upper breakeven point.
* Payoff of short strangle looks exactly opposite of long straddle
* Profit are restricted to the extent of net premium recieved
* Profits are maximum as long as stock stays within the two strike price
* Losses are potentially unlimited.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Put call parity
* Relationship between short put and long call option with same strike price, expiration date and underlying
* Can be applied for American option when exercised at expiration
* Combining the graph of long call and short put ended up getting a resultant graph of future
* When put call parity doesn't hold it means there is a opportunity of arbitrage means one can make riskless profit 
* Whenever equality doesn't hold between the LHS and RHS of equation one can less the bigger side and buy the lower side of the equation. Which is also clear from common sense that selling costlier and buying cheaper will result in a profit.
* The profit what we are making from these two respective portfolio representing both sides of equation will always remain same with time and change in strike price.

Author: vedant11#6910
Content:
A few tips to improve social skills and connect with people more:

1. Pay attention and listen with conscious effort, slowly you'll be curious about every person's story
2. Ask questions if you are curious, even if it might feel stupid. You can always state that you are learning something, or don't know about something but are curious. The other person feels nice too when someone goes out of their way to show interest.
3. Try to speak slowly and clearly if the person is meeting you for the first time. A good eye contact helps to know whether he/she can catch-up with what you have to say.
4. Ask the person to 'wait a min' if you have something in your mind, instead of just zoning out and missing out what he/she said.
5. Wear a smile : )

Author: rupz#8120
Content:
Planning day is fine but how you plan your day is equally important. Sometimes the lack of productivity and not ticking off all the daily tasks is because of poor goal setting or no goal setting at all. Here is a technique of goal setting. Set SMART goals.
1. S= Specific. Goals need to be clear and specific.
2. M= Measurable. There must be an identifiable metric to measure the progress of the goal.
3. A= Attainable. The difficulty of the goal should be not too much such that it becomes unattainable. Neither set too easy goals.
4. R= Relevant. Goals should be relevant to your dreams.
5. T= Time Bound. Have a deadline for your goals. That means you know when to celebrate your success. 
Hoping this technique helps you setting your goals in better way:)

Author: jai2201#7481
Content:
Hey @Damini , I skimmed through your code, This is great effort for the this fullStack project. Good Job.
I would want you to iterate this in few more ways - 

Naming conventions followed were pretty good.
Code was clean.
Data base structure was pretty straight to the point.

1.) Try to write functional views instead of class views in your few of the initial projects in Django -- Functional views gives you a more clear idea of what's going on in the back end side of the view functions.

This is a bit more advanced thing -- 

2.) Try to make a customised User model of your own -- instead of using the by-default User model of Django, while there's no harm in that but yeah -- as you dive deep with things, you'll see that Django's by-default User model is not sufficient enough in itself  (as you cannot add any of your customised fields):))

You can move ahead with your goals for now and try to keep these points in mind while proceeding further :))
Good Luck.

Author: vedant11#6910
Content:
My experiences while starting conversations with strangers, it differs a bit, from talking to someone you know:

- try to be friendly and start off slow. pick up the signs the person might be busy, caught up with something other to worry about, or simply not interested. you can push your luck and try again if he/she's not interested. it's best to leave in many scenarios.
- always be clear with the purpose of your questions or statements. communicate well. don't make the person second-guess or wonder about why did you just ask/say that thing. e.g. if you ask someone if they smoke ganja, ask them you wanted to know about any remarkable experiences. don't let  them second guess that you're side-eyeing their habit.
- always thank and offer help, water, food or any treat (everyone likes chocolates) for taking up their time. humans a books, access to their stories is a privilege and a learning experience.

Author: Ishu#8694
Content: We perceive 'Self doubt' as a curse. But if we change our perspective towards it, it would turn into felicity. Self doubt holds strong energy beneath it, we just have to find a technique through which we can harness its energy. We should make self doubt our friend instead an enemy. Through this we are able to use its energy in our betterment. Self doubt tells us about our weak points, our triggers. Once we make a bond with our self doubt, we'll be able to figure out the ways to eliminate our triggers.

Author: satyam_dubey#3256
Content:
Hey Aman! Overthinking is pretty common problem...

There is just one way to end overthinking...

Just one...

And that is to do the thing.
Once you do it, you get to know the reality behind it.

Overthinking is a mindset Problem...
You just need to shift your self talk from 'agar ye kiya aur ache se nhi hua toh?' 

To 'chal karke dekhte hai'.

Takes time.. because you have got habituated to it. 
But, you need to correct you thought everytime it comes.

Overtime you'll gain control. 
Hope it helps!
Cheers 🌟

Author: rupz#8120
Content:
Hey ginie.. Great attempt. I loved the background a lot. Want to know where did you get it from.  

Other than that, it can be improved in font type and font size/font weight
1. Font type of 'join us' can be improved. It looks strange. Other than that you have used 4 different font types in a single poster. Try to limit fonts to 2.
2. Font size and font weight are important for heirarchy. Font weight of Sneha singh can be increased. Date and address font size can be decreased a bit. Color of Last line makes it highlighted the most when it's heirarchy is last. 
You can work on these changes.

Author: rupz#8120
Content:
And for the tshirt, Seems decent,  Here are few suggestions you can work on-
1. The logo seems too big for the tshirt. And it's position is too up and right cornered which makes front side bit noisy. Backside looks clean and sober. But explorin is written twice and both times it's heirarchy is on the top. You can lower it's heirarchy on the back side. You can take inspirations from other tshirt from internet.
2. The suggestions are almost similar for hoodie too. On the back of hoodie, the cursive font doesn't suit much. You can work on picking better font.

Author: mewtwo#5793
Content: Hello everyone!! I have completed my Goal 6 based on Neural Networks.. and it was fun exploring how it works... it feels more like we are training our computer as a child.. like.. assume a picture of dog.. we told a child to predict what it could be.. and suppose he says dog.. then in regards to acknowledge him that he was right we give him some sort of reward or if he guesses wrong.. we correct him or give some sort of punishment to stop that action again.. Similar goes with computer.. while training we gave him feed back which back propogates through neural networks and update the weights used for decision making... having many layers of neural network enable us to predict complicated situations too.. all in all it is a very powerful tool to predict things.. ❤️‍🔥

Author: bhawna#2966
Content:
aren't afternoons  full of passion ? or maybe different for all . i hope u all know what's ur peak passionate time of the day and if not , know it ASAP.  I just wanted to share my few techniques of completing daily tasks more .
 1.** writing tasks on paper **- involving sensory organ is helpful and will give you a whole diff vibe on completing tasks
2. **100/120 approach instead of 80/100**- completing 100% goals while aiming for 120% is more useful and accomplishing than trying to complete 80%of the tasks of the day . plan 20% extra tasks which can fall under Pomodoro time span . 

it is a **win-win approach** as one is able to complete the major and minor tasks (which are always in the back of the mind ) and this also helps in pushing the limits of human potential . 

the ongoing challenge is a golden opportunity to apply this and please lemme know if this helps or you couldn't understand it all .

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
Hii Hemant
I'm so so happy to see you coming up with this submission in your first attempt itself🤩 🤩 

1. Glad to see you following the whole process from defining the goal, talking to dreamers and finding their pain points, figuring out solutions to those pain points and defining the success metrics and pitfalls of the proposed solution.
2. The pain points you found through dreamers are pin point and exactly what we have found out in our research. This shows how well and disciplined you were in your interviews.

Some improvements you should work on:
1. Talk to more dreamers, so that you can find out which pain point is the most painful and needs to be solved first(Prioritization of pain points)
2. Mention more details of the dreamer in the user persona, such as their year of study, stage of exploration ( exploring to find passion, specialising in passion, monetizing in passion), details about how the dreamers use the platform
3. Think of more than one solution for each pain point and then select the best one.
4. Define why the metrics you have mentioned is a success metric of the solution

Author: Somesh#3376
Content: Hello everyone, I am just about to start my 2nd year of college...my first sem was online, so I didn't even realise the importance of being in college and the importance of exploring..So I enjoyed my first sem celebrating the fact that I was finally in IIT and was done with all jee stuff...And in the 2nd sem, when I realised the need to explore and how my future is affected by my decisions, I was forced to focus on acads.....Now when I am done with acads, and I want to finally start on my journey of dream college life, I still have many problems like.. Which field should I pursue?...I look around, and many of my friends have started something or the other...so am I too late? What if I fail in a field that I try to explore? Will there be time left to start over again?........And then there is that big problem of procrastination..

Author: jai2201#7481
Content:
Absolutely No!
If you're passionate about something which is being followed by other people as well this doesn't mean that you're a part of rat-race, 

What rat-race means is just -- you're doing something or trying to pursue a field just because of a reason that "Everyone else is doing that", without knowing the reason why do YOU want to pursue this field!

If you're clear enough about WHY do you want to pursue a field then you should surely go ahead and explore it without worrying about the number of people following it :))

ps - I'm into web-dev. too, which I think is a field of high-traffic but it doesn't mean that I'm into rat-race, same follows for Competitive programming, Finance, Quant, etc.

Author: argus#2468
Content:
Hey Hemant
I found your submission very interesting with the simplified approach you followed. 🔥 
You covered all the crucial steps required in approaching towards finding the optimal solutions to the problem.
I definitely agree with keshav's feedback and the need to elaborate all the points in order to provide a better understanding to the viewer and self.

For the user persona section, 
You could also try asking the dreamers, questions based on your predictions/assumptions about the problems they might face( hence try to simplify the review process for them), then try to characterize the response for support in future analysis. 
Following that, you could provide multiple solutions to the problems on the basis of their characteristics.
Another thing, I felt the comparison of solutions could be there, to prioritize the solutions on the basis of the impact they will have. Hence, providing a better executional approach.

Eager to see the next iteration!

Author: notsosuresudhanshu#2270
Content:
It’s a double edged sword for me. But the midnight suits best for me. In the anticipation of working hard at night and collecting motivation all day and finally working hard with successfully accomplishing the goal gives me the utmost satisfaction and i sleep like a baby after that. But if it doesn’t goes as planned due to overwhelming of tasks and sometimes my anticipation becomes the weight on my shoulder. If it doesn’t goes as planned that’s a painful thing for me. So i would say **80-100** thing works for me but i take care if even that isn’t accomplished that’s okay too. I should be at peace as long as self-talk negatively.
P.s. It was great delving into my habits.
Thankss!!

Content:
The latest thing  I learned was about working of venture and PE Funds 
1. Their structure comprising of GPs and LPs
2. Their functioning in different phases of funding,investing, holding and exiting. 
3. Distribution of profits after funds exits the investment 
a. First LPs get their capital back along with promised hurdle rate 
b. Then same goes for GPs.
c. After that profits Distribution among them such that LPs have to pay 20 % to GPs as commission.

Author: Rushikesh#2088
Content:
Hello everyone! I am from NIT Nagpur. My second year is going to start in about 15 days.
In the first year what I observed in the college is that majority of people are just busy doing things that even they even are not clear about. As we say, the rat race! Very few talk about exploring new things. Most of the clutter is around getting good cgpa, getting good jobs and getting settled.
 The problem I face in college is that I want to explore, I want to do things even if they're not done traditionally in the college and I don't find a good peer group that encourages exploration. 
Second problem is I don't have a clear path to explore since there is no one to look upto for guidance in my college. I hope I am at the right place to start exploring now!

Author: Ani Jeenwal#3194
Content:
So here are some learnings
Product management is basically concerned with upto which extent the product meets the need of the customer and make him happy.
This field also includes some sort of product design, product marketing and product development.Also studied about product life cycle.
In creating a opportunity hypothesis, I have studied that basically how to plan a product, analysing the data and metrics, planning to achieve the goal and most importantly deeply analyse the need of the customer.
In validating the hypothesis,after planning the product this step involves analysis of product like taking feedbacks and reviews, internal validation, external validation etc.

Author: satyam_dubey#3256
Content:
Hii bro! Mere saath bhi hota hai yaar... Parents still think like it's school time.. exams khatam hone ke baad apan free ho gye h.

So, iska ek sahi aur ek thoda faulty solution h..

Agar tum frustrate hote h because wo tumhe kuch na kuch kaam de rhe.. toh isse kuch solve nhi hoga.

A better solution is to explain them in their words. 
Unko bata do for example ki mujhe coding mein interest hai aur college mein project/assignment mila hai ki agle ek month mein finish Krna hai warna marks nahi milenge..

They'll understand more in terms of exams, assignments, project etc.

So, ye bol do aur agar jarurat pade toh thoda pressure badhane ke liye tell them ki sabhi log mujhse bahot aage hai... 

Finish nahi kiya jaldi toh piche ho jaunga...
Parents won't ever let you lag behind.

Toh they'll begin to understand :) 
Hope it helps!

Cheers 🍻

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
🌟 Streak Day #2
Had a lot of realizations today, with most of them being still unbaked😬 

Wanted to share one of those feelings:
In the past I used to think about what it takes to be great. I used to question whether my actions have a chance to make me great. I used to have a feeling that something's missing in my actions or in my judgement of whether I can be great. And am happy that I was being honest about my doubts.

And now for the last couple of days, that thought+feeling of what it takes to be great is again resurfacing. But this time, I am feeling the increase in clarity on what it takes and what it would take for me, thanks to me realizing the importance of peak performance and mindset through being surrounded by my comrades @Explorin @satyam_dubey @jai2201 @rupz @utkarsh @Kishlay @Divyansh @sparkling @Prashant Jindal 

I know I am very unclear in expressing myself here, but I need to extract out my emotions more and more. So, would keep on sharing my unbaked feelings
😬

Author: himanshu#6252
Content:
hi @rizul 
Definitely, you are not wrong. There are a lof of ways you can learn software engineering. But it all depends you want to pace up the learning or take time for that. The current goals include flask as it is the simiplest framework to start a server and then program rather than node/express or python/django or java/spring.

We just want to give you a smooth transition into software engineering as fast as possible. Flask is a day project. Django takes more than a week. Similar with others.

We recommend learn python as it will help you in Data Science, Finance, Product Management and what not. It has a very broad application in various industries.

Author: himanshu#6252
Content:
also, we are glad you know that you dont have interest in Flask and testing. 
That’s what the exploration is for. It would help us evaluate your interest and thus we can help you make better decisions for that.

Content:
Hey everyone , this is Karan from IIT Roorkee . I think rat race exists in every arena , it exists because of human nature of requiring assurance for each and every thing . Since some people might have done well in a  field ,others start following them since they know there are high chances of them landing in the same place if they follow similar path , where there’s uncertainty only few take a chance . And once those few crack it and they find an easier way to reach there other rats follow them. 
My biggest problems in college life are - Time management , dilemma while setting priorities and lack of clarity
